verbose_text: Very weak inhibitory activity of Thymus vulgaris oil with minimum inhibitory concentration of 2670 mug/mL on oral Streptococci were also reported by Imelouane et al. 9 Thymus vulgaris oil analysis by gas chromatography-mass spectrometry carried out by these investigators exhibited no carvacrol and presence of very low amount of thymol (0.24%).
